Class YahooMediaHash

Represents the hash of a binary media object.

Syntax
[Serializable]
public class YahooMediaHash : IComparable
Remarks

This entity can be assocaited multiple times to a media object as long as each YahooMediaHash instance has a different Algorithm.

Algorithm

Gets or sets the algorithm used to create this hash.

Declaration
public YahooMediaHashAlgorithm Algorithm { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
YahooMediaHashAlgorithm

A YahooMediaHashAlgorithm enumeration value that indicates the algorithm used to create this hash. The default value is None, which indicates that no hash algorithm was specified.
Remarks

If no algorithm is specified, it can be assumed that MD5 was used to create this hash.
